HEADWORD: Diplomatist
<hw>Di*plo"ma*tist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>diplomatiste</ets> a student of diplomatics.]</ety> <def>A person
employed in, or skilled in, diplomacy; a diplomat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In ability, Avaux had no superior among the numerous able
